<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | Code Square LLC"
  description="Privacy Policy for Code Square LLC website and contact form."
>
  <main class="legal-page">
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container legal-content">
        <a href="/" class="legal-back">‚Üê Back to Home</a>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: February 16, 2026</p>

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>
          When you use our contact form, we may collect your name, email address, subject, and
          project summary.
        </p>

        <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
        <p>
          We use submitted information to respond to inquiries, discuss potential projects, and
          provide requested services.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Sharing of Information</h2>
        <p>
          We do not sell personal information. We may use service providers (for example, email
          delivery providers) only to operate our business communications.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Cookies and Analytics</h2>
        <p>
          We may use cookies and similar technologies for core website functionality, performance,
          and analytics. Where required, we will obtain consent before using non-essential cookies.
        </p>

        <h2>5. International Data Transfers</h2>
        <p>
          Your information may be processed in countries other than your own. Where required, we use
          appropriate safeguards for cross-border data transfers.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          We retain inquiry information as needed for business communication, legal obligations, and
          record-keeping.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Security</h2>
        <p>
          We use reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect information submitted
          through the site.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
          Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, or delete personal
          information. Contact us to submit a request.
        </p>

        <h2>9. California Privacy Notice</h2>
        <p>
          If you are a California resident, you may have additional rights under California law,
          including rights to know, delete, and correct certain personal information, subject to
          legal exceptions.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Changes to this Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy from time to time. Any updates will be posted on this page with
          a revised &quot;Last updated&quot; date.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For privacy questions, contact us at
          <a href="mailto:info@thecodesquare.com">info@thecodesquare.com</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
